    "summary": "Monday’s flurries on Mt Ruapehu turned out to be a bit more than that. It was a welcoming surprise when webcams showed more than a dusting, and Turoa reported a tidy 10cm on Tuesday morning. You should also wake up to a fresh dusting of up to a couple of centimetres over the Southern Lakes this Wednesday morning from light overnight snowfall.",
